title: Imagen 3

openaiSpec.name: generate_image_with_google_imagen_3

prompt.description: A detailed description of the image to be generated. Be specific about the subject, style, composition, lighting, colors, and any other relevant details.

negativePrompt.description: Describe elements or concepts that should *not* be included in the generated image. This helps to refine the output and avoid unwanted results.

openaiSpec.description: Generates images using Google's Imagen 3 model.  Provide a detailed prompt and, optionally, a negative prompt to guide the generation.

userSettings.name: PROJECT_ID
userSettings.label: Google Cloud Project ID
userSettings.description: Your Google Cloud project ID. Can be found in the Google Cloud Console (https://console.cloud.google.com/)

userSettings.name: REGION
userSettings.label: Google Cloud Region
userSettings.description: The Google Cloud region to use (e.g., us-central1).  Available regions can be found at https://cloud.google.com/vertex-ai/docs/general/locations

userSettings.name: model
userSettings.label: Imagen 3 Model
userSettings.description: Select the Imagen 3 model to use. -002 is the newest, -001 is an earlier version, and -fast-001 is optimized for speed. Default: imagen-3.0-generate-002

userSettings.name: sampleCount
userSettings.label: Number of Images
userSettings.description: The number of images to generate (1-8). Default: 1

userSettings.name: aspectRatio
userSettings.label: Aspect Ratio
userSettings.description: The aspect ratio of the generated image. Default: 1:1

userSettings.name: imageQuality
userSettings.label: Image Quality
userSettings.description: The image quality. Choose enhanced for better quality. Default: standard

userSettings.name: personGeneration
userSettings.label: Person Generation
userSettings.description: Controls whether the generated images can include people.  `dont_allow`: No people. `allow_adult`: Adults only. `allow_all`: All ages. Default: allow_adult

userSettings.name: safetySetting
userSettings.label: Safety Setting
userSettings.description: Controls the safety filters. `block_low_and_above`: Strongest filtering. `block_medium_and_above`: Balanced filtering (Default). `block_only_high`: Fewer filters. `block_none`: Minimal filtering (restricted access).

overviewMarkdown:
🖼️ **Google Imagen 3 Image Generator**

Generate images from your text prompts using Google's Imagen 3 model! ✨

**Important: This plugin requires you to configure a Google Cloud OAuth 2.0 connection. Follow these steps carefully:**

1.  **Create a Google Cloud Project:** If you don't have one already, create a new project in the Google Cloud Console: [https://console.cloud.google.com/](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2.  **Enable the Vertex AI API:** In your Google Cloud project, go to "APIs & Services" > "Enabled APIs & services" and enable the "Vertex AI API".
3.  **Create OAuth Credentials:**
    *   Go to "APIs & Services" > "Credentials".
    *   Click "+ CREATE CREDENTIALS" and choose "OAuth client ID".
    *   **Application type:** Choose "Web application".
    *   **Name:** Give your OAuth client a descriptive name (e.g., "TypingMind Imagen Plugin").
    *   **Authorized JavaScript origins:** `https://www.typingmind.com` or your self-hosted URL.
    *   **Authorized redirect URIs:** `https://www.typingmind.com` or your self-hosted URL.
    *   Click "Create".
    *   You'll be given a **Client ID** and a **Client Secret**, which can be used in the Auth Settings. **Keep the Client Secret *secret*.**

Note that if you get an error like *this app is not verified by google* during the authentication process, you can authorize yourself by going to your Google Cloud's Console >  "APIs & Services" > "OAuth Consent Screen" > "Audience", then click "ADD USERS" under Test Users section and enter your email address.
